ur.com/YFmQW.jpg\" alt=\"enter image description here\"><br>\n<sup>Fig.1. Left: sciatic nerve overview. Right: Sacral plexus. Source: <a href=\"http://www.mbmyoskeletal.com/learning/sciatica/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Manchester Bedford Clinic<\/a><\/sup><\/p>\n\n<p>Hence the sciatic nerve does not come into contact with the bowel and intestines located ventrally in the abdominal cavity (Fig. 2).<\/p>\n\n<p><img src=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/TFhkv.jpg\" alt=\"enter image description here\"><img src=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/wAtzt.jpg\" alt=\"enter image description here\"><br>\n<sup>Fig.2. Left: sciatic nerve in detail showing dorsal location. Right: Intestines ventrally situated in abdominal cavity. Source: <a href=\"http://www.mbmyoskeletal.com/learning/sciatica/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Manchester Bedford Clinic<\/a> and <a href=\"http://health.bwmc.umms.org/patiented/articles/colon_cancer_normal_anatomy_000126.htm\" rel=\"nofollow\">University of Maryland<\/a><\/sup><\/p>\n\n<p>Pain in the sciatic nerve (sciatica) is often caused by compression or entrapment by muscles, tendons, and other soft tissues along the nerve path <a href=\"http://www.mbmyoskeletal.com/learning/sciatica/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Manchester Bedford Clinic<\/a>. <\/p>\n","answer_id":34421,"question_id":34420,"up_vote_count":5,"last_edit_date":1432244543}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/34420/what-is-the-distance-between-the-sciatic-nerve-and-the-colon-at-the-closest-poin","migrated_from":{"other_site":{"icon_url":"http://cdn.sstatic.net/Sites/health/img/apple-touch-icon.png","audience":"medical specialists, students, dietitians, and anyone with health-related questions","favicon_url":"http://cdn.sstatic.net/Sites/health/img/favicon.ico","site_type":"main_site","logo_url":"http://cdn.sstatic.net/Sites/health/img/logo.png","api_site_parameter":"health","open_beta_date":1429747200,"site_state":"open_beta","related_sites":[{"site_url":"http://meta.health.stackexchange.com","api_site_paramet