h I feel hungry?","body":"<p>Why I feel hungry after brushing my teeth in morning?<\/p>\n\n<p>I usually have my dinner in between 9 to 10 at night and then I sleep at 12. Sometimes I wake up at 6 in morning and then I go to brush my teeth. After brushing my teeth I feel hungry. Why I feel hungry after brushing my teeth? And this hunger is gone even if I take few(about 5-10) biscuits. <\/p>\n\n<p>Now one day I woke up at 6 am and then I have not brushed my teeth till 11 am and on this day I was not feeling hungry till 10 am.<\/p>\n\n<p>So is there any chemical in toothpaste which triggers hunger? One thing which I can notice is that before doing brush there is saliva in mouth whereas just after doing brush there is no saliva or very less amount of saliva in mouth. <\/p>\n\n<p>Even after chewing a gum for 30  min I feel the same hunger. So is there any relation between toothpaste and chewing gum? <\/p>\n","question_id":40990,"tags":["human-biology","teeth","saliva"],"score":-2,"accepted_answer_id":40997,"down_vote_count":3,"closed_reason":"primarily opinion-based","is_answered":true,"view_count":70,"up_vote_count":1},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/d117d782e1f2d2706ddabe1febee315c?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":835,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/835/robert-long","reputation":251,"display_name":"Robert Long"},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/ab24c0e23c30888c23e2d4fe9991cf2b?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":57,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/57/jonsca","reputation":3367,"display_name":"jonsca","accept_rate":100},"score":0,"post_id":2305,"edited":false,"creation_date":1337347680,"comment_id":3091,"body":"I think Shep had more of the right idea in his <a href=\"http://meta.biology.stackexchange.com/a/260/57\">answer<\/a> to your Meta question about this, I don&#39;t know how you can maneuver this to make it more constructive