ntally.<\/p>\n","answer_id":40958,"question_id":40956,"up_vote_count":0},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/8338f9b96b1c61599df745d61145b0c2?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":15878,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/15878/243","reputation":959,"display_name":"243"},"score":2,"is_accepted":true,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/56b4833d86d3cccc3ccfd6eeaf0b767e?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":14946,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/14946/mdperry","reputation":2645,"display_name":"mdperry"},"score":0,"post_id":40967,"edited":false,"creation_date":1448412721,"comment_id":69267,"body":"Yes, if you poured acrylamide into a horizontal slab mold it would take a very long time to polymerize, AND that top surface would dry out (unless you had a buffer layer on top of it, or plastic wrap, or similar)."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://graph.facebook.com/724354877676809/picture?type=large","user_type":"registered","user_id":17473,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/17473/sunboyharry","reputation":139,"display_name":"sunboyharry"},"score":0,"post_id":40967,"edited":false,"creation_date":1448514262,"comment_id":69353,"body":"Why does the agrose slippery out from the bottom if it runs vertically?"},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/8338f9b96b1c61599df745d61145b0c2?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":15878,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/15878/243","reputation":959,"display_name":"243"},"score":0,"post_id":40967,"reply_to_user":{"profile_image":"https://graph.facebook.com/724354877676809/picture?type=large","user_type":"registered","user_id":17473,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/17473/sunboyharry","reputation":139,"display_name":"sunboyharry"},"edited":false,"creation_date":1448561588,"comment_id":69385,"body":"@sunboyharry Agarose does not adh